      <abstract>
        <p>* Roundup of advertising account changes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>* Netfolio, New York, an online financial services company, to McKinney &amp; Silver, Raleigh, N.C., part of MarchFirst, as the first agency of record to handle its account. Billings were estimated at $10 million to $20 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>* Netfolio, New York, an online financial services company, to McKinney &amp; Silver, Raleigh, N.C., part of MarchFirst, as the first agency of record to handle its account. Billings were estimated at $10 million to $20 million.</p>
        <p>* JobDirect.com, Stamford, Conn., a Web site that posts entry-level jobs that is owned by Korn/Ferry International, to the Langworth Pantel Group, White Plains, as first agency of record. Spending was estimated at $5 million.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
